# Merge `/ytDownloader` + `/instaDownloader` â†’ Unified `/downloader`

Combine both video download commands into a single `/downloader` command that auto-detects the platform and validates the URL is actually a downloadable video before proceeding.

## Proposed Changes

### Handler module â€” consolidate into one file

#### [MODIFY] [videoDownloader.py](file:///d:/My%20Business/My%20Projects/On-Going/Omni%20Telegram%20Bot/bot/handlers/ytDownloader.py)

Rename [ytDownloader.py](file:///d:/My%20Business/My%20Projects/On-Going/Omni%20Telegram%20Bot/bot/handlers/ytDownloader.py) â†’ `videoDownloader.py` and make it platform-agnostic:

- Rename all comments from "YOUTUBE DOWNLOADER" â†’ "VIDEO DOWNLOADER"
- Add a `validate_video_url(url)` function that uses `yt_dlp.YoutubeDL.extract_info()` in simulate mode to verify the URL is a real video supported by yt_dlp, **not** just any random link. Returns [(True, extractor_name)](file:///d:/My%20Business/My%20Projects/On-Going/Omni%20Telegram%20Bot/bot/main.py#642-650) or [(False, error_message)](file:///d:/My%20Business/My%20Projects/On-Going/Omni%20Telegram%20Bot/bot/main.py#642-650).
- Keep the same [fetch_formats](file:///d:/My%20Business/My%20Projects/On-Going/Omni%20Telegram%20Bot/bot/handlers/ytDownloader.py#53-74), [download_video](file:///d:/My%20Business/My%20Projects/On-Going/Omni%20Telegram%20Bot/bot/handlers/instaDownloader.py#79-112), [build_quality_keyboard](file:///d:/My%20Business/My%20Projects/On-Going/Omni%20Telegram%20Bot/bot/handlers/ytDownloader.py#13-48), [_fetch_and_show_qualities](file:///d:/My%20Business/My%20Projects/On-Going/Omni%20Telegram%20Bot/bot/handlers/instaDownloader.py#117-163) functions â€” they already work for both YouTube and Instagram via yt_dlp.
- Update [_fetch_and_show_qualities](file:///d:/My%20Business/My%20Projects/On-Going/Omni%20Telegram%20Bot/bot/handlers/instaDownloader.py#117-163) to accept a generic `quality_state` parameter instead of hardcoding `BotStates.waiting_for_quality` or `BotStates.insta_waiting_for_quality`.
- Update the error message in [_fetch_and_show_qualities](file:///d:/My%20Business/My%20Projects/On-Going/Omni%20Telegram%20Bot/bot/handlers/instaDownloader.py#117-163) from "YouTube video" to a generic "video URL".

#### [DELETE] [instaDownloader.py](file:///d:/My%20Business/My%20Projects/On-Going/Omni%20Telegram%20Bot/bot/handlers/instaDownloader.py)

No longer needed â€” `videoDownloader.py` handles all yt_dlp-supported sites.

